Class OD

  • java.lang.Object
    • bayou.od.OD

  • public class OD
extends Object
    A Service Locator library.

    See package doc.

    This class (OD) is a namespace containing some interfaces and static methods.

      • get

        public static <T> T get(ClassType<T> type,
                        Object... tags)
                 throws OD.NotFoundException
        Lookup an object by (type,tags).

        The local binding list is searched before the global binding list. If a binding is found to match (type,tags), the supplier is invoked to return a `T` value. Otherwise, `NotFoundException` is thrown.

        Throws:
        OD.NotFoundException - if binding is not found for (type,tags)
        See Also:
        get(Class, Object...)

      • bind

        public static <T> OD.BindingBuilder<T> bind(Class<T> clazz)
        To add a global binding.

        This method is equivalent to bind(ClassType) by wrapping the `Class` as `ClassType`; see ClassType.of(Class).

        Example usage: 

             OD.bind(Foo.class).to(foo);

      • bind

        public static <T> OD.BindingBuilder<T> bind(ClassType<T> type)
        To add a global binding.

        This method return a builder; when the builder finishes, a binding is created and added to the global binding list.

        Example usage: 

             OD.bind( ClassType.of(Foo.class) ).to(foo);
        See Also:
        bind(Class), ClassType

        Add the binding to the global binding list.
